transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, Kevin. This is Michelle.

Speaker 2: Hi, Michelle. How are you doing?

Speaker 1: Good. How are you?

Speaker 2: I'm okay. I had spoke with someone earlier. You guys were trying to get a hold of me. I didn't know it until the day when I was looking. The doctor was reaching out to me. The information I gave you...

Speaker 1: Did you put in a refill today?

Speaker 2: A refill? No, not a refill. What I did was call to find out why you were contacting me. The doctor was reaching out to me. They basically texted me and told me and asked me to call. I called. He wanted to know my blood pressure average. I gave him the wrong information. I called my doctor and find out exactly what my blood pressure average is. The last time I went and seen him, my blood pressure was a little high. It was 173 over 80. That's because I work midnights. I had went to him after I got off from work. My average is 148, between 148 and 156. It usually stays in between there.

Speaker 1: No, I'm saying it averages like 146 or 148. Then the over number is 80.

Speaker 2: That's always 80, but that other one goes up and down, because I work midnights.

Speaker 1: That's what I was just trying to make sure that he got the right information, so hopefully he won't be turning me down.

Speaker 2: Okay, perfect. I'm writing this down. I'm giving him a text message. It's 146 over 80 to 148 over 80?

Speaker 1: Right, like that.

Speaker 2: It depends on if I go to him if I've been working all night. I work midnight, so that raises your blood pressure.

Speaker 1: Then I smoke, too. That also raises your blood pressure, just so that he has the accurate information.

Speaker 2: That was an interesting answer. Why did he call me and ask me that?

Speaker 1: Let me call my doctor. That made me feel better, to be able to give him the accurate information.

Speaker 2: All right, perfect. I wrote him that, so then he'll probably approve your prescription by tomorrow morning.

Speaker 1: Okay, perfect. Thank you so much.

Speaker 2: Yeah, not a problem. I'm glad we got that cleared up for you, Kevin.

Speaker 1: Absolutely. Yes, I appreciate it, too, because I had told her the last reading, and that was because I had went to him overnight after work, and my blood pressure was a little high, so I just wanted to clarify that.

Speaker 2: Perfect.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you so much.

Speaker 2: No problem, Kevin. Have a great day.

Speaker 1: You, too, now. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: All right, bye.
